_json.gridTitle: Home Tour: Pamela Pierce's Houston House
_json.description: The designer's apparently fearless use of white everywhere, however, does give pause. It shouldn't, Pierce says, even though her pale furniture keeps company with two dogs and visiting grandchildren. "If it's linen, you just wash it." She has her fabrics pre-washed and dried so that they are pre-shrunk. "My slipcovers in the family room get washed about once a week.
